FBIS4-26514 "drchi121_m_94002" FBIS-CHI-94-121 Daily Report 21 Jun 1994 Military History of Party Organs in Army Published History of Party Organs in Army Published OW2206145194 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1041 GMT 21 Jun 94 OW2206145194 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service Chinese BFN [By correspondent Bian Yanshi (0593 1750 1395)] [Excerpt] Beijing, 21 June (XINHUA) -- A series of books entitled An Historical Data for the Organization of the People's Liberation Army [PLA] of the Communist Party of China [CPC] were recently published by the Long March Publishing House. The series was compiled by the General Political Department of the PLA under the instruction of the CPC Central Committee and the Central Military Commission. The series consists of six volumes, covering all the historical periods of the party -- Land Reform Struggles, War of Resistance Against Japan, Liberation War, Basic Completion of Socialist Reform and Beginning of Overall Socialist Construction, Cultural Revolution, and New Period of Socialist Modernization. The series boasts complete information, accurate historic records, scientific compiling styles, and concise use of the language. It details leading and working party organs of all troops under the PLA, their relationship and reasons for organizational changes, lists of key leaders, and party and administrative work of key leaders, including terms of their service. The series comprehensively and systematically reflects the establishment, development, and evolution of the party organs in the army, as well as the history of the party's efforts to exert absolute control of the army through its organizations. [passage omitted]
